  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda \u0d85\u0daf\u0dca\u0db7\u0dd6\u0dad \u0dc0\u0ddb\u0dbb\u0dc3\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A mysterious virus is spreading in India",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "With the spread of a new type of influenza, the Indian government has issued an advisory to all states.",
        "This viral disease, which mainly affects minors, causes large red blisters and has come to be known as tomato flu.",
        "According to a statement issued by India's health ministry on Tuesday, the disease is prevalent in the country's southern states, with more than 82 cases involving children under the age of five. The first case of flu was reported from Kerala on May 6.",
        "Although scientists believe the new flu is a type of foot-and-mouth disease (HFMD), they have so far failed to identify the exact nature of the pathogen."
      ],
